<TITLE> Govt hikes energy prices </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 30 (bdnews24.com)  The government has hiked fuel prices effective from Tuesday, the energy ministry said in a statement. According to the new decision, octane will cost Tk 90 per litre, up Tk 23 from Tk 67; petrol Tk 87, up Tk 22 from Tk 65; and diesel Tk 55, up Tk 15 from Tk 40. The chief adviser's special assistant M Tamim, who overseas power, energy and mineral resources ministry, told bdnews24.com that: "We had no alternative to hiking fuel prices due to an abnormal rise on the global market." The government earlier increased fuel prices on April 2 last year. The government also raised the prices of kerosene to Tk 55 from Tk 40 per litre. bdnews
